snippet.textDisplay: My mom died when she was 40, her & my dad were together for 25 years. I was 13 & my brother had just turned 7. I just remember feeling like it wasn’t real, like this was a dream & truly not happening. I also remember my dad being so odd in the sense that he was there physically but he couldn’t really hear or see anything else & spiritually he was absent. My brother telling members of our family that she was going to wake up. Till this day there is nothing more painful to me than the pain I feel when I miss my mom & think about what her life would’ve been now. I wish Vanessa, her daughters & the rest of the families peace, good memories, & that they feel the love that the person who passed away felt for them all their lives.

snippet.textDisplay: Thank you for saying that Adrian. I lost my husband 9 months ago when I was 9 months pregnant with our 3rd son. It is so important for people to remember the mourning and grieving doesn't end after the memorial service. As Tamera said, grief is the most difficult thing to travel through and there is no way around it, only through it. What helps is family and friends remembering Vanessa and traveling this road of mourning alongside her to give her strength when she feels weak. Everyone said to me, "You are so strong! You're taking care of your babies." But most days I don't feel strong, I just have to get out of bed and do it because my boys need me. My husband, soulmate, and best friend, the person who took care of me is no longer here. So it's such a devastating loss. I can't even begin to imagine how deep that loss is for Vanessa having also lost her sweet Gigi. May God cover and protect her, her girls, and Kobe's family & friends. And every single person who knew and loved those souls on that helicopter.
snippet.textOriginal: Thank you for saying that Adrian. I lost my husband 9 months ago when I was 9 months pregnant with our 3rd son. You're taking care of your babies." But most days I don't feel strong, I just have to get out of bed and do it because my boys need me. I can't even begin to imagine how deep that loss is for Vanessa having also lost her sweet Gigi. May God cover and protect her, her girls, and Kobe's family & friends. And every single person who knew and loved those souls on that helicopter.

Vanessa Bryant is one heck of a strong woman. If I'm not mistaken, she and her sister, Sophie were instrumental in putting this together.
Vanessa and all of the victims families need to sue the HELL out of the company that owned the helicopter. Years before this most recent crash, the NTSB made a recommendation to the FAA that helicopters like this one should have a Terrain Awareness
and Warning System. The NTSB also recommended to the FAA these helicopters should have a Flight Data Recorder.
Although the FAA ignored both recommendations, the helicopter company should have complied with the NTSB suggestions.
God Bless all of the families.

snippet.textDisplay: Loni always has to say the controversial things.. smh. Kobe's relationship with his parents is no one's business but his and theirs. For her to say that ppl should fix things while they are here... Sometime's people have toxic family member's who don't respect their decisions and lifestyle and they have to cut people out. It takes more than one person reaching out, it takes all sides being on the same page and willing to respect boundaries and lifestyles. Go back and watch Kobe's 2004 interview on ESPN. He explains in detail what his parents did to him and how they didn't approve of his marriage. I don't blame him at all. Sacrifices are made to protect your kids and your life. People who wanna be apart of your life- WILL be apart of that. - May he rest in peace!
